      • setRenderOntologyLists

        public void setRenderOntologyLists(boolean renderOntologyList)
        Specifies whether or not ontology lists should be rendered after frame section keywords. Ontology lists are not part of the Manchester Syntax specification - they are an extension for use in editing tools and the like. The default behaviour is not to render the ontology list. An example of an ontology list is: Class: A SubClassOf [in X, Y, Z] B. Where X, Y and Z are ontologies. This indicates that A SubClassOf B occurs in ontologies X, Y and Z.
        Note that, for backwards compatibility, setting setRenderExtensions(boolean) to true will also cause ontology lists to be rendered (along with other extensions).
        Parameters:
        renderOntologyList - Whether or not to render the ontology list for each section. true if the list should be rendered, otherwise false. The default behaviour is false.

      • writeEntityNaryAxioms

        public void writeEntityNaryAxioms(OWLEntity entity)
        Writes out the Nary axiom frames that contain the specified entity as an operand. These are either, DisjointClasses, EquivalentClasses, DisjointObjectProperties, DisjointDataProperties, EquivalentObjectProperties, EquivalentDataProperties, SameIndividual or DifferentIndividuals axioms that have more than two operands, one of which is the specified entity.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity. Not null.
